{
  "stem": "15962.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The liquidation of the family camp, the death of my father, sending my mother into the unknown, and my transfer with 90 other boys to a new environment was really a watershed in my life.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was suddenly alone, without my parents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I still carried some hope that, when this all ends, my mother will come back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I knew that my father perished.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the hope of someday being reunited with my mother helped me to a great degree to survive in subsequent conditions, which became worse and worse as time passed by.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The camps became-- the condition-- general conditions in the camps became worse. primarily.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the realization that I am alone was not very comforting.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was, then, not quite 14 years old.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There-- one reason that we were able to survive is that there was a great deal of [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] reliance on each other and help and the feeling that we are in the same boat and that we need to support each other.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Out of the 89 boys that were selected by Mengele on July 4, about 35 [SIGHS] or 40 are known to have survived the subsequent nine months, eight months.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Two thirds died in those following months, from-- mostly from starvation and disease.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was, again, lucky that I not only was selected to-- to live but to survive the next period.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What were you doing there?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What kind of work were you doing?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I mentioned earlier, of the 89 boys was selected for lighter works.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So this was, again, a change that, before we were really not given specific tasks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, we all had to work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The majority was used to pull wagons.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were-- there was a lack of horses.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
